<TITLE> New NBR boss urges collectors to reach revenue targets </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Oct 24 (bdnews24.com)  The country's top taxman Wednesday paid a surprise visit to Chittagong Customs House, an official said. The new chairman of the National Board of Revenue, Md Abdul Majid, called on officials to work hard to reach the revenue targets. He held a meeting with the customs officials at the Customs House. Commissioner (imports) Md Lutfar Rahman, commissioner (exports) Margub Ahmed and other VAT and income tax officials were present at the meeting. Lutfar Rahman told bdnews24.com that the NBR chairman had inspired his deputies to work with honesty and sincerity to achieve the year's Tk 12,000 crore revenue target. He said the NBR's new boss asked customs officials to be courteous with taxpayers. Chittagong Customs House collected Tk 2,750 crore in duties, about Tk 100 crore above target, in the first three months of fiscal 2007-08, Rahman said. The government appointed Abdul Majid NBR chairman on Oct 18, replacing Badiur Rahman, who was transferred to the food and disaster management ministry. bdnews24.
